      },
      "date": "2015-02-06 00:02:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhat about inheriting the timestamps from the original MDT inode at layout swap time (e.g. MDS setattr on the OST objects before doing the swap)?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "660f383ef8102a360361efcbc766d337344b79f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 1,
        "name": "Robert Read",
        "email": "robert.read@intel.com",
        "username": "rread",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2015-02-06 00:09:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI agree with Andreas, it seems like this should be done during layout swap. Logically, the  layout swap should only be changing the layout, and not the inode or contents, so the swap should ensure that.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bf8d57bc350c4d72cd38064cd5907321c833fb9a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2015-02-06 02:20:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> What about inheriting the timestamps from the original MDT inode at layout swap time (e.g. MDS setattr on the OST objects before doing the swap)?\n\nI thought we should avoid having the MST perform synchronous RPCs on behalf of clients.\n\nWhat you propose is also a good deal more complicated than what's in this change.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
